                "comment_count": 0,
                "committer": {
                    "date": "2026-05-11T04:51:50Z",
                    "email": "bjodah@gmail.com",
                    "name": "Bjorn"
                },
                "message": "Fix duplicate C++ conversion utility emission for vector defaults (gh-6981)\n\nRoot cause: CppClassType.create_to_py_utility_code and create_from_py_utility_code\ncalled CythonUtilityCode.filter_inherited_directives(env.directives) where env\nis the local analysis scope.  When two different code paths request the same\nvector.to_py helper (e.g. an extension-type property getter and a function's\ndefaults getter), they may pass scopes with different directive values for\ndirectives that do not affect the generated C helper at all — most notably\n'binding', which is set to False by copy_for_internal() for the defaults-getter\nscope introduced by the PEP-669 commit (ed2b40be6cad).\n\nBecause CythonUtilityCode.__eq__ includes compiler_directives in the equality\ncheck, two CythonUtilityCode objects with identical impl but binding=True vs\nbinding=False are considered distinct, bypassing deduplication in\ninject_utility_code_stage and emitting two identical C function bodies.\n\nFix: use env.global_scope().directives as the directive source in both\ncreate_to_py_utility_code and create_from_py_utility_code for CppClassType.\nModule-level directives are always the same for all call sites within a single\ncompilation, so the resulting CythonUtilityCode objects are equal and the\nexisting set-based deduplication in inject_utility_code_stage suppresses the\nduplicate emission.\n\nAdds a compile-mode regression test (tests/compile/cpp_vector_to_py_dedup_T6981.pyx)\nthat reproduces the minimal trigger shape from the bug report: a template cppclass\nproperty returning vector[T] combined with a def function taking vector[double]\nwith a default [] argument.\n\nTests:\n- python runtests.py -vv --backends=cpp cpp_vector_to_py_dedup_T6981\n- python runtests.py -vv --backends=cpp cpp_stl_conversion cyfunction_defaults_cpp cpp_templates_nested fused_cpp\n\nCo-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>",
